Half string formalism and regularization  

We start from full string functions  
 with Dirichlet boundary conditions at  and discuss their
split string formulation in the interval . Such
functions have a Fourier expansion with only sine  modes in the full
string formalism. By contrast, the corresponding problem in the matter
sector involved only cosine  modes because of Neumann boundary
conditions at . We collect the basic formulae in the
appendix . The essential step was the construction of the
regularization which is needed to avoid the associativity
anomaly. We give a regularization of the ghost sector for the sine mode
expansion which is compatible with the previous results.

