a new generalization of Neumann coefficients since the new expression
includes arbitrary spectral parameters and arbitrary . To compare to the
Neumann coefficients computed through conformal field theory, the open
string limit () is taken at the end.
Through analytic and numerical methods it is shown that these very different
looking forms of Neumann coefficients are indeed the same. This successful
test of MSFT provides confidence about its correctness and shows that MSFT
is an alternative tool for computation in string theory.

