Numerical comparison of Neumann coefficients 
 

In this subsection we compare the generalized Neumann coefficients derived
algebraically in the Moyal star formalism for any 
  with the independent computation from the point of view of conformal
field theory valid at . We
summarize the Neumann coefficients computed from CFT in appendix 
, together with some differences in the convention.

In we have already given an analytic proof that our algebraic
expression of Neumann coefficients coincides with the exact value in
 in the limit, by comparing the spectroscopy of Neumann coefficients.
Namely, in our case by diagonalizing the matrix 
 we diagonalize the Neumann coefficients
for -point vertices, since they all depend on the same matrix  The
eigenvalues obtained in this way for the case of the 3-point vertex in the
limit  coincide with the
corresponding eigenvalues obtained from Neumann spectroscopy in
.

A numerical study provides another approach to confirm that the Moyal star
and CFT calculations agree in the limit. In the following numerical analysis
we show that there is agreement in the limit, and furthermore that there is
a clear universal behavior of the approach to the limit as a function of 
. In the tables given in appendix  we give the MSFT
results for the numerical values of the Neumann coefficient 
 in the matter sector, and the Neumann
coefficient  in the ghost sector for 
