the tables we write the ratio with their limiting value, 

and ,
where the limiting value is taken as the CFT value given in. The
tables at different values of  clearly show the convergence 
 
Namely in the open string limit, the Neumann coefficients derived
algebraically in MSFT becomes identical with their analytic value computed
in CFT.

We note that the convergence of the Neumann coefficients of the ghost sector
is much slower than those of matter sector. However log-log plot of 
